    "description": "The AccessData Secure Network Communications FIPS 140-2 Object Module is a cryptographic module that operates as a multi-chip component library positioned between the FIPS 140-2 validated OpenSSL FIPS Object Module version 1.1.2 API and a host application. The AccessData Secure Network Communications module provides to any AccessData application that incorporates it, electronic encryption designed to prevent unauthorized access to data transferred across a physical or wireless TCP/IP network.",
